3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves combinatorial arguments and mathematical proofs, which are typical of discrete mathematics.
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper does not explicitly deal with computational complexity, but the problem of finding codewords with certain properties can be seen as a computational problem.
5. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper does not involve geometry, but the concept of componentwise product can be seen as a geometric operation on vectors.
